<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link><description>World News Today: Read the latest world news headlines, Current International breaking news world wide. In depth analysis and top news headlines world wide.</description><language>en-gb</language><lastBuildDate>2026-07-08T21:01:27+05:30</lastBuildDate><atom:link type="application/rss+xml" rel="self" href="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/rssfeeds/296589292.cms"/><copyright>Copyright:(C) Wed, 08 Jul 2026 21:01:27 IST Bennett Coleman &amp; Co. Ltd, http://in.indiatimes.com/policyterms/1554651.cms</copyright><docs>http://syndication.indiatimes.com/</docs><image><title>World News, Today World News, Latest International News, World Breaking News, Trending News of World - Times of India</title><url>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/507610.cms</url><link>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world</link></image><item><title><![CDATA[Towering trees more than 200 feet tall may not be as vulnerable to drought as scientists thought, new study reveals how Southeast Asia’s dipterocarps efficiently move water]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132266398.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Recent studies unveil that massive trees in Southeast Asia possess remarkable adaptations in their water transport mechanisms. These trees, known for reaching impressive heights, can effectively draw water upward, defying the challenges posed by gravity. This groundbreaking research, focusing on Malaysia's dipterocarps, shows that taller trees feature broader xylem vessels, offering fresh insights into their resilience amidst climate change.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/towering-trees-more-than-200-feet-tall-may-not-be-as-vulnerable-to-drought-as-scientists-thought-new-study-reveals-how-southeast-asias-dipterocarps-efficiently-move-water/articleshow/132266398.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/towering-trees-more-than-200-feet-tall-may-not-be-as-vulnerable-to-drought-as-scientists-thought-new-study-reveals-how-southeast-asias-dipterocarps-efficiently-move-water/articleshow/132266398.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T20:30:24+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132266657,imgsize-456202.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Connor Murphy cause of death: New details emerge after influencer's tragic death in Thailand]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132266092.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Fitness influencer Connor Murphy, 32, died in Thailand as authorities investigate the circumstances surrounding his death. Police said witnesses reported erratic behaviour before the incident, while investigators later recovered unused syringes and unidentified pills during a search. Murphy's girlfriend denied seeing him use drugs. An autopsy and toxicology tests are underway to determine the official cause of death, as fans mourn the popular fitness creator.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/connor-murphy-cause-of-death-new-details-emerge-after-influencers-tragic-death-in-thailand/articleshow/132266092.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/connor-murphy-cause-of-death-new-details-emerge-after-influencers-tragic-death-in-thailand/articleshow/132266092.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T20:12:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132266092,imgsize-176914.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Lust for murder': German doctor who killed 15 patients gets life term; suspected in 76 more deaths]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132266276.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/lust-for-murder-german-doctor-who-killed-15-patients-gets-life-term-suspected-in-76-more-deaths/articleshow/132266276.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/lust-for-murder-german-doctor-who-killed-15-patients-gets-life-term-suspected-in-76-more-deaths/articleshow/132266276.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T20:03:10+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132266346,imgsize-22730.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Telegram 'drug rape' network that shocked Germany! How secret codes were used to assault women]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132266042.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[German prosecutors have discovered disturbing Telegram groups where members discussed plans for sexual assaults and drugging. They cleverly disguised their actions using terms like 'cars' and 'fuel.' Years of posts revealed numerous attacks on incapacitated individuals, with several members already convicted. Ongoing investigations aim to uncover the full extent of this network, raising significant concerns about the misuse of online platforms and their global repercussions.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/telegram-drug-rape-network-that-shocked-germany-how-secret-codes-were-used-to-assault-women/articleshow/132266042.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/telegram-drug-rape-network-that-shocked-germany-how-secret-codes-were-used-to-assault-women/articleshow/132266042.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T19:57:17+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132266231,imgsize-69950.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Mysterious 'space balls' twice the size of basketballs wash ashore on Australian beach, scientists say the discovery is more common than many people think]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132264663.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Metallic spheres have mysteriously appeared on an Australian beach, sparking local alarm. After thorough investigation, authorities determined the oddities were actually remnants of space debris—specifically pressure vessels from rocket launch vehicles that survived their fiery return to Earth. With the surge in space explorations, experts predict that encounters with such debris will become more frequent as launches increase.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/mysterious-space-balls-twice-the-size-of-basketballs-wash-ashore-on-australian-beach-scientists-say-the-discovery-is-more-common-than-many-people-think/articleshow/132264663.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/mysterious-space-balls-twice-the-size-of-basketballs-wash-ashore-on-australian-beach-scientists-say-the-discovery-is-more-common-than-many-people-think/articleshow/132264663.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-08T19:05:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/ms